      "writtenOn": "2020-03-23T19:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "suggestion: slices of test case structs can be somewhat annoying to debug (e.g. setting breakpoints). Because of this, I prefer to do\n\ntest :\u003d func(name string, ...) {\n   t.Run(name, func(t *testing.T) {...}\n}\n\ntest(\"all parameters missing, returns error\", missing, missing, \"required image matching parameter not found\")\ntest(\"...\")",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1312,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 1312,
        "endChar": 6
      },
      "revId": "bef63587a60cc2f0a619e9e53cbd896050ccc9e7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "34907cae_7b67ad18",
        "filename": "gold-client/go/goldclient/goldclient_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 1312,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-24T05:08:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ll leave them as is for the same reasons as in https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/276277/11/gold-client/go/imgmatching/factory_test.go#185, namely the complex arguments and the variable argument list.\n\nRegarding the debugging aspect, IntelliJ and other IDEs support setting conditional breakpoints; that is, breakpoints that will only pause execution if a certain boolean expression evaluates to true. To set a conditional breakpoint in IntelliJ, first set the breakpoint as usual, then right click on it to enter the desired boolean expression: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/iVHM2cOsO84. This is how I\u0027ve been debugging the tests in this CL chain.",
      "parentUuid": "da5d3a07_8fa3b605",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1312,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 1312,
        "endChar": 6
      },
      "revId": "bef63587a60cc2f0a619e9e53cbd896050ccc9e7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
