      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe it would make sense to combine this and the negative case into\nTestCloudClient_MatchImageAgainstBaseline_SobelFuzzyMatching_AlreadyTriaged\n\nThere\u0027s a lot of duplicate code between the two cases, which could be put into a test function\n\ntest :\u003d function(name, expectations, expectedReturnValue) {\n  t.Run(name, func(t *testing.T) {...}\n}\n\ntest(\"positive returns true\", expectations.Baseline{\n\t\ttestName: {\n\t\t\tdigest: expectations.Positive,\n\t\t},\n\t}, true)\n\ntest(\"negative returns false\", expectations.Baseline{\n\t\ttestName: {\n\t\t\tdigest: expectations.Negative,\n\t\t},\n\t}, false)\n\nIt helps emphasize the differences betweeen the two tests.\nIf you like this approach, please also do it for the fuzzy matching above.",
